transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I bought Viagra from you before and would like to order some more.

Speaker 1: Sure. I need your name and zip code.

Speaker 2: Terry, C-A-R-Y, Lindsay, L-A-N-D-S-A-Y, 9-8-3-6-5.

Speaker 1: That's my zip code. It might come up for 9-8-0-2-2.

Speaker 2: Thank you. One second.

Speaker 1: Okay. I have PO Box 217 in Enumclaw.

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Okay. Small world. I grew up in Maple Valley.

Speaker 2: Okay. So you last ordered 40 pills. You want to do 40 again, sir?

Speaker 1: How much is it?

Speaker 2: Same as last time, $163.95 is what you paid that time and would pay this time.

Speaker 1: Sure.

Speaker 2: Okay. I have a card that ends in 4878. Do you want me to use that or a different card today?

Speaker 1: That'll work.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay. I got a decline on that.

Speaker 2: Decline?

Speaker 1: Yeah, on the MasterCard.

Speaker 2: I thought I had a balance. Let me give you a different card. I thought I had a balance on that. It was a gift card, so it might be –

Speaker 1: Oh, I got you.

Speaker 2: I'm going to go Plan B here.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right. Let's go. You ready?

Speaker 1: I'm ready.

Speaker 2: 4046.

Speaker 1: 8252.

Speaker 2: 0494.

Speaker 1: 2229.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Expiration?

Speaker 1: 1029.

Speaker 2: And the security code?

Speaker 1: 848.

Speaker 2: We are all set. This is going to be shipped out here within a day or two typically, so you're all good to go.

Speaker 1: You'll be emailed a tracking link once it ships as well.

Speaker 2: Thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: Welcome. Have a good one.

Speaker 2: Thanks.
